## (1)(a) IETF Function and Working Groups

> Explain the function of the IETF (Internet Engineering Task Force) and name three of its working groups. *(2 marks)*

---

The **IETF** develops and promotes **Internet standards**, particularly the TCP/IP protocol suite. It publishes specifications as **RFCs** (Request for Comments).

**Three IETF Working Groups:**

| Working Group | Focus |
|---------------|-------|
| **MANET** | Mobile Ad-hoc Networks routing |
| **6LoWPAN** | IPv6 over Low-Power Wireless |
| **DMM** | Distributed Mobility Management |

